<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8885> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8885" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 729" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7874> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7874" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cos. 195. Leg., lieut. 191. In MRR 1.355, refer also to Phlegon Trall. 31, FGrH 2 B, no. 257, p. 1174; Zon. 9.19.9.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2466> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2466" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Q. Fabius Labeo succeeded L. Valerius Flaccus. On Valerius, see Münzer, Gent. Val. 39, no. 17." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2464> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2464" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 40.42.6 and 11-12." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2337> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2337" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "These won a hotly contested election (Liv. 39.40-41; Plut. Cat. Mai. 16.1-6; cf. Nep. Cato 1; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 48f., 122, 456f.). They exercised a censorship noted for its severity, in the revision of the roll of the Senate, whence Cato removed L. Flamininus, Cos. 192, in the review of the knights, when he took the horse from L. Scipio, Cos. 190, and in the leasing of the public contracts (Cic. Sen. 19; Nep. Cato 2.3; Liv. 39.42.5-44.9; Val. Max. 2.9.3; 4.5.1; Plut. Cat. Mai. 17-19; Flam. 18.3-19.4; Auct. Vir. Ill. 47.4; 53.2; cf. FOR 1.35-53, 174-186).{375} After the death of Scipio Africanus, L. Valerius Flaccus became Princeps Senatus (Liv. 39.52.1-2). On Cato, see D.- G., 5, no. 15; on Valerius, Münzer, Gent. Val. 39, no. 17." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2270> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2270" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Established a Latin colony at Bononia (Liv. 37.57.7-8, cf. 47.2; Vell. 1.15). See 190, Special Commissions." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2232> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2232" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Created to supplement Placentia and Cremona (Liv. 37.46.10-11; see 189, Special Commissions)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2196> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2196" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Legatus (Liv. 36.17.1) under Glabrio at Thermopylae and in the war against the Aetolians (Liv. 36.19.1, 22.7, 27.3-8, and 28.8; cf. Polyb. 20.9-10, with the title {Gr}; App. Syr. 18; and Tribunes of the Soldiers, on Cato). See Münzer, Gent. Val. 39, no. 17." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2104> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2104" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proconsul in Gaul (Liv. 34.46.1) until succeeded, and won a victory over the Insubres at Mediolanum. Cf. Grueber, CRRBM 1.120f.; 2.300; Cesano, Stud. Num. 1 (1942) 184f. See Münzer, Gent. Val. 39, no. 17." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2067> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2067" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Nep. Cato 1.1; 2.1; Liv. 33.42.7; 34.1.7, and 5.2; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 48f., 121, 452f.; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd. (Festo et Flacco); Chr. Pasc. ({Gr}); Oros. 4.20.12; Cassiod.; and on Cato, Cic. Sen. 19. Valerius was assigned Italy as his province and carried on war with the Gauls (Liv. 33.43.5; 34.22.1-3, and 42.2-4; Plut. Cat. Mai. 10.1), while Cato waged an important and successful war in Spain (Liv. 33.43.5; 34.8-9, and 11-21; Val. Max. 4.3.11; Frontin. Str. 1.1.1, and 2.5; 3.1.2, and 10.1; 4.7.31, 33, and 35; App. Ib. 39-41; Plut. Cat. Mai. 10-11; Auct. Vir. Ill. 47; Zon. 9.17; cf. FOR 1.158-166; Nep. Cato 2.1; Cic. Div. in Caec. 66; Plin. NH 14.91). He vowed an aedicula to Victoria Virgo (Liv. 35.9.6; cf. Grueber, CRRBM 2.303, 574; Cesano, Stud. Num. 1 [1942] 182f.). On Cato, see D.- G., no. 15; Lübker, no. 4; and on Valerius, Münzer, Gent. Val. 39, no. 17." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2062> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2062" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "L. Valerius Flaccus succeeded M. Cornelius Cethegus.  Liv. 33.42.5. On Valerius, see Münzer, Gent. Val. 39, no. 17." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1963> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1963" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See Münzer, Gent. Val. 39, no. 17." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1952> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1952" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "All served under Purpurio in Gaul (Liv. 31.21.8). On Valerius, see Münzer, Gent. Val. 39, no. 17." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1951> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1951" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "It is chronologically possible to identify Valerius with the Consul of 195, who was Curule Aedile in 201 and Pr. in 199; and there is no record of another L. Valerius Flaccus who meets the conditions." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1948> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1948" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Though the names of these Legates are doubted by Münzer (RE) because the details of the accounts are drawn from annalistic sources, some are indubitably historical (e. g. Laetorius, and Valerius), and all should be listed." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1905> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1905" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 31.4.5-6. On Quinctius, see Lübker, no. 12; on Valerius, Münzer, Gent. Val. 39, no. 17." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1535> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1535" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Served under the Consuls in the capture of Hanno's camp at Beneventum (Liv. 25.14.6; Val. Max. 3.2.20). See Münzer, Gent. Val. 39, no. 17." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1534> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1534" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Münzer (Gent. Val. 59) would list this Tribune of the Soldiers among those invented by Valerius Antias for the greater renown of his family. The style of the passage resembles the late annalistic, but the names need not be fictitious." .
